    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span style=\"font-family:Jost\">Zhirafa drones have a simple claim to fame: they're cheap, durable, and easy to repair, making them an essential tool of most organizations within the Red Decades.</span></p><p>WalkMeks are bipeds, possessing the latest and greatest in Opposable Thumb technology. They aren't fast, but their fully actuated fingers are capable of poking things, picking up items, and even opening doors!</p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;scrollbar-width:thin;scrollbar-color:var(--color-scrollbar) var(--color-scrollbar-track);margin:0.5em 0px;color:rgb(13, 11, 12);font-family:Jost;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;white-space:normal;background-color:rgb(234, 234, 234);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial;text-align:start\"><span style=\"font-family:Jost\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;scrollbar-width:thin;scrollbar-color:var(--color-scrollbar) var(--color-scrollbar-track);font-weight:550\">Uses the RatSec WalkMek Drone statblock.</strong></span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;scrollbar-width:thin;scrollbar-color:var(--color-scrollbar) var(--color-scrollbar-track);margin:0.5em 0px;color:rgb(13, 11, 12);font-family:Jost;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;white-space:normal;background-color:rgb(234, 234, 234);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial;text-align:start\"><span style=\"font-family:Jost\">Has two hands for holding things, but only comes equipped with a Drone-Integrated Stun Stick, which is a @UUID[Compendium.night-city-gang-and-corp-mook-pack.NCGangsnCorpsItems22.o9PXaS85Tv3bWuiO]{Stun Stick} installed in one of its hands that can't be removed. Always equipped with a front-mounted <a class=\"content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-link data-uuid=\"Compendium.cyberpunk-red-core.core_gear.Item.clCxd7qkp2olsKii\" data-id=\"clCxd7qkp2olsKii\" data-type=\"Item\" data-pack=\"cyberpunk-red-core.core_gear\" data-tooltip=\"Gear Item\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;scrollbar-width:thin;scrollbar-color:var(--color-scrollbar) var(--color-scrollbar-track);cursor:pointer;--content-link-background:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);background:rgb(221, 221, 221);color:var(--cpr-text-normal);padding:1px 4px;border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark-tertiary);border-radius:2px;white-space:nowrap;word-break:break-all\">Video Camera</a>.</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;scrollbar-width:thin;scrollbar-color:var(--color-scrollbar) var(--color-scrollbar-track);margin:0.5em 0px;color:rgb(13, 11, 12);font-family:Jost;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;white-space:normal;background-color:rgb(234, 234, 234);text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial;text-align:start\"><span style=\"font-family:Jost\">See Controlling Drones in the Associated Homebrew document for more details on how to control the drone, once purchased.</span></p>"
